            <notesStmt>
                <note type="summary">
                    
                        
                            <p>This is a letter from a representative of the Royal Library of Belgium to  Mrs J. R. Green (Alice Stopford Green) (1847-1929), wife of historian John Richard Green (1837-1883). Stopford Green was a nationalist, involved in the Howth gun-running, a historian in her own right, and founder of African Society 1915. The writer inform her that the Belgian government has created a special department to which will be entrusted all documents relating to the War. The collection will form the publicly accessible Archives of War at the Royal Library of Belgium, Brussels. He asks for her assistance in securing  material relating to the Irish question and the Rising. </p>
                        
                    
                </note>
